One of the men walked into the local police station where he handed over body parts and told police that he's tired of being a cannibal. DURBAN - Four men have appeared in the Escourt Magistrates Court in KwaZulu-Natal on charges of cannibalism and murder. On Friday, one of the men walked into the local police station where he handed over body parts and told police that he's tired of being a cannibal. The suspect then led officers to a house where more evidence was found. Preliminary investigations led authorities to the other suspects, one of whom is believed to be a traditional healer. The National Prosecuting Authority's Natasha Karraact said: “They were remanded into custody and will appear again on Monday 28 August for a formal bail application. The charges they face at the moment are conspiracy to commit murder and murder.”